column3: Eating habits [Do you skip breakfast more than once a week?]
column4: Eating habits [Do you skip lunch more than once a week?]
column5: Eating habits [Do you skip evening meals more than once a week?]
column6: Eating habits [Do you skip meals and snack instead on most days?]
column7: Fruit and vegetables [Do you eat more than 5 portions of fruit and/or vegetables every day?Remember that fruit juice only counts as 1 portion a day, regardless of how much you drink. The same applies to dried fruit. Potatoes count as starchy foods and not as vegetables. As a guide, a portion is about a handful.]
column8: Fruit and vegetables [Do you eat more than 4 different varieties of fruit each week?]
column9: Fruit and vegetables [Do you eat more than 4 different varieties of vegetables each week?]
column10: Fat [Do you choose low-fat products when available?]
column11: Fat [Do you choose baked, steamed or grilled options when available, rather than fried foods (such as crisps and snacks, or fish and chips)?]
column12: Fat [Do you opt for lean cuts of meat or remove visible fat – for example, removing the skin on chicken or the rind on bacon?]
column13: Fat [Did you eat any oily fish last week? Examples of oily fish include salmon, mackerel, herring, sardines, trout, and fresh tuna.]
column14: Fat [Do you include some unsalted nuts and seeds in your diet?]
column15: Starchy foods [Do you base your main meals around starchy foods? For example, potatoes, pasta, rice or bread.]
column16: Starchy foods [Do you regularly choose wholemeal bread or rolls rather than white?]
column17: Starchy foods [Do you regularly eat wholegrain cereals, with no added sugar?]
column18: Starchy foods [Do you regularly include pulses in your diet? For example, beans and lentils.]
column19: Sugar [Do you regularly eat sugar-coated breakfast cereals or add sugar to your breakfast cereals?]
column20: Sugar [Do you add sugar to your drinks?]
column21: Sugar [Do you regularly drink sweet fizzy drinks?]
column22: Sugar [Do you regularly eat cakes, sweets, chocolate or biscuits at work?]
column23: Salt [Do you regularly add salt to food during cooking?]
column24: Salt [Do you regularly add salt to meals at the table?]
column25: Salt [Do you regularly eat savoury snacks at work?For example, crisps or salted nuts.]
column26: Salt [Do you regularly eat pre-prepared meals? For example, pre-prepared sandwiches, ready meals or canned soups.]
column27: Salt [Do you regularly eat processed meats such as ham or bacon, or smoked fish?]
column28: Salt [Has your GP advised you that you have high blood pressure?]
column29: Drinks and alcohol [Do you drink plenty of fluids at regular intervals during the working day?]
column30: Drinks and alcohol [Do you opt for a variety of different drinks, including water, at work?]
column31: Drinks and alcohol [Do you avoid sugary fizzy drinks?]
column32: Drinks and alcohol [Do you drink less than 2-3 units of alcohol a day if you’re a woman, or less than 3-4 units of alcohol a day if you’re a man?]
